We define metonyms as words which can be used in place of one another when they have a domain-specific relation (Gerstl (1991)) 2.2 Using Lexical Semantics for Response Representation Our goal in building a scoring system for free-responses is to be able to classify individual responses by content, as well as to determine when responses have duplicate meaning (i.e. , one response is the paraphrase of another response).


